
[1]monstrous

   MON'STROUS, a. [L. monstrosus.] Unnatural in form; out of the common
   course of nature; as a monstrous birth or production.

   1. Strange; very wonderful; generally expressive of dislike.

   2. Enormous; huge; extraordinary; as a monstrous highth; a monstrous
   tree or mountain.

   3. Shocking to the sight or other senses; hateful.

    MON'STROUS, adv. Exceedingly; very much; as monstrous hard; monstrous
                                   thick.

   And will be monstrous witty on the poor.

   [This use is colloquial and vulgar.]
